snippet.textDisplay: Couple of tips: the brink guard isn`t actually a parry, parry comes later, you have to spec into it. Brink guard just reduces the amount of stamina you lose when blocking. No difference in damage blocked between just holding guard vs brink guard. Also, Strength does nothing for you with dual wields, just keep enough Strength to cover your equipment weight.. Spec heavily into Endurance first early on, to get stamina and stamina regen. This isn't 100% like a Souls game, focus is a lot of combos and you can play way more aggressively than Souls... For your gear, focus on getting the best set bonuses you can, and keeping all your gear to current or close to current player character, all the other stats you can reroll later on...

snippet.textDisplay:
Hell yeah, this game is tight been going hard with it and definitely thought of you while I've been playing through it. You definitely gotta play through it so you can find your baddies. This is also the easiest/ or at least the most forgiving type of souls game I feel, haven't even tried easy mode. Though that doesn't mean there isn't a challenge. Once you get that block timing down its pretty sweet, though some people have lightning quick attacks, but once you learn to perfect block those its pretty sweet. Sometimes I find the quick attacks easier to counter compared to the slow/ lag like attacks cause I feel the anticipation building waiting to counter the slow attacks. The quick attacks you just get into the momentum of their swings and lock into that rhythm to block.
Also the spear, that's the main weapon I've been using since I got it.
